<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-07-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-07-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="581" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d581">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">841.6363/425</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the British Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Lindsay</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-07-20">July 20,
                                    1936</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: Reference is made to your note
                                of July 6th, requesting confirmation that the Government of the
                                United States does in fact regard Great Britain as a reciprocal
                                country under the Mineral Leasing Act of 1920.</p>
                            <p>I have the honor to inform you that the Department of the Interior is
                                now prepared to recognize Great Britain as a reciprocal country
                                under the Mineral Leasing Act of 1920. A copy of the letter from the
                                Acting Secretary of the Interior in this connection is
                                    enclosed.<note n="11" xml:id="d581fn11">Not printed.</note>
                            </p>
                            <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Cordell Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>